A: The problem is that you are using the same DataSnapshot object in the loop and in the line where you add the value to the list. You should use the dataSnapshot1 object instead of dataSnapshot.
Here is the corrected code:
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This will correctly add all the values from the children of the DataSnapshot to the names list.

